# IoT-Based Laser Security System: Real-Time Intrusion Alerting via ESP32 and Telegram Bot

## Overview

This project implements an IoT-based laser security system using an ESP32 microcontroller, laser transmitter, LDR sensor, and Telegram Bot integration. The system continuously monitors a laser beam and detects intrusions when the beam is interrupted.

Upon intrusion detection, the ESP32 activates a local alarm and instantly sends real-time notifications to authorized users through Telegram Messenger. The system also provides periodic status updates indicating normal operation.

## Features

* Real-time intrusion detection using Laser and LDR
* Instant Telegram alert notifications
* Multi-user Telegram notification support
* Audible buzzer alarm
* Visual LED indication
* NTP-based time synchronization
* ESP32 Wi-Fi connectivity
* Low-cost and scalable security solution

